  "question": "Looking at VaR, did the risk that JPM faced in the second fiscal quarter of 2023 decrease compared to the same period in the prior year?",
  "answer": "Yes, the risk faced by JPMorgan Chase in the second fiscal quarter of 2023 decreased compared to the same period in the prior year. Average total Value-at-Risk (VaR) decreased by $7 million for the three months ended June 30, 2023, compared with the same period in 2022 [PAGE 85]. This decrease was predominantly driven by risk reductions impacting Credit Portfolio VaR and fixed income [PAGE 85]. The table on the same page confirms this, showing an average total VaR of $47 million for the quarter ended June 30, 2023, compared to $54 million for the quarter ended June 30, 2022 [PAGE 85].",
